{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6c554e63-31a8-47ef-b487-4fb1f69178c5","content":"Here are the breaking changes for your specific code:\n\n---\n\n**① Dockerfile — update tags**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:10.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:10.0 AS build\n```\n.NET 10 defaults to Ubuntu 24.04 (Noble). Verify `libgdiplus`/`libc6-dev` package availability in that base.\n\n---\n\n**② global.json**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"10.0.100\" } }\n```\nAnd update `<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>` in your `.csproj`.\n\n---\n\n**③ NativeInterop.cs — `DllImportSearchPath.System32` on Linux**\n.NET 10 tightens non-Windows behavior: `System32` no longer silently falls back to default search paths, so your P/Invoke will fail at runtime on Linux. Fix:\n```csharp\n[LibraryImport(\"mylib\")]\n[DefaultDllImportSearchPaths(\n    DllImportSearchPath.AssemblyDirectory | DllImportSearchPath.ApplicationDirectory)]\ninternal static partial int ProcessData(byte* input, int length);\n```\nThis also migrates from `DllImport` to the source-generated `LibraryImport` (recommended since .NET 7).\n\n---\n\n**④ ComHelper.cs — `IDispatchEx` removed**\n`System.Runtime.InteropServices.Expando.IDispatchEx` is removed in .NET 10. The cast won't compile. Use `dynamic` instead:\n```csharp\ndynamic dispatch = comObject;\n// access members dynamically\n```\n\n---\n\n**⑤ NativeAOT — `$ORIGIN` rpath no longer set by default**\n.NET 10 NativeAOT no longer embeds `$ORIGIN` in the ELF RUNPATH on Linux. Native library resolution next to the binary will break. Add to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <LinkerArg Include=\"-Wl,-rpath,'$ORIGIN'\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n---\n\n**⑥ Single-file publish** — the command is unchanged, but verify native dependencies (`mylib`, `libgdiplus`) sit alongside the published output, as extraction behavior for native libraries may differ in 10.0.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1a03a24d-43e9-4c18-840